## 1. User Journeys

Before routes, think about journeys. A journey is the sequence of screens a user walks through to complete a goal.

### Customer Journey
```
Lands on app
    ↓
Sees queue listing (public)
    ↓
Wants to join → prompted to login/register
    ↓
Logs in → redirected back to queues
    ↓
Joins queue → gets token number
    ↓
Watches queue status in real time (WebSocket)
    ↓
Token called → goes to counter
    ↓
Done (entry marked served by operator)
```

### Operator Journey
```
Logs in
    ↓
Sees their assigned queues
    ↓
Opens a queue → sees waiting list
    ↓
Clicks "Call Next" → advances queue
    ↓
Current token updates everywhere (WebSocket broadcast)
    ↓
Repeat
```

### Admin Journey
```
Logs in
    ↓
Dashboard → overview of all queues + stats
    ↓
Create new queue
    ↓
Manage operators → assign to queues
    ↓
Override queue (pause, disable, reset)
    ↓
View analytics
```

